                    </div>
                    <span>don't bother buying this book.<p>For me, it was a bummer, too much ado about hiring practices, and the author does not escape his bias after having worked for Microsoft 10 years.<p>There are too many inaccuracies, like Microsoft has won the database wars, Microsoft has won the networking wars, Windows NT is  "clearly superior to Linux", etc, etc.....</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great book, but ended strangely</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
